<br>
When I bought PoP a week after it was released I was disappointed to find that the rare undead shitz I run into can't be charmed by my level 54 spell.  Several months later, however, after our guys started getting level 65 spells it became apparent that the level 65 charm would once again allow us to charm @#%$ for better than average exp.  I do agree that the amount of exp gained by a necromancer versus the risk is sorta (ok maybe really BUT only because of FD! Heh) unbalanced but I wouldn't go so far as saying charm kiting hasn't always been a better option for soloing.  Just because in previous expansions most people didn't have the guts  (the so called &quot;skill&quot; that certain individuals seem to claim to have more of perhaps?), gear, mana, or patience to learning how to do so doesn't mean it hasn't always been a viable option for exping.  <br>
<br>
I agree that charm kiting, especially in the case of a necromancer, gives exp in a somewhat unbalanced amount but I would say they need to look at some other options.  They just need to nerf the exp gained or something to make it so that the exp gained while charm kiting is slightly more than the normal method of killing.  I'll share some numbers from my experience in soloing.  I usually average around 1 aa per 30 ish minutes in the long run while charm kiting within the Crypt of Decay.   I'm sure as a necromancer I can gain exp much faster than an enchanter.  While using a conventional pet to kite while using dots I can do 1 aa per 1 ish hour within the Halls of Honor.  It's just more tedious.<br>
<br>
-My numbers on the Crypt of Decay is based on doing a /play constantly and looking at my aa gained.  I suppose I could gain more exp but death is almost a sure thing while charm kiting PoP mobs so need to leave a little exp in normal exp if yer wanting to keep level 65.<br>
<br>
-My numbers from HoH is based on the mobs having a 20 min repop timer and me being able to keep 6 spawns cleared with a little bit of med time in between repop sessions. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=melahmitofsaryn>Melahmit of Saryn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:green;'>Tavern Patron</span></span><br>  Posts: 123<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(3/31/03 11:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3187.topic&index=103>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Charm Nerf</span><hr size=1> Ohh yea in regards to using charm to beat the shits out of named mobs and thus making the other fools who can't do the same cry with envy they should just make the fvcking mobs regen faster.  It's pathetic to have the named stuff regen at a pedestrian level while the other mobs zoom by to full health in a few ticks.  People with enough brain cells would figure to use that to their advantage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jehmgryphonkin>Jehm Gryphonkin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:pink;'>Tavern Floor Sweeper</span></span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(4/1/03 3:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3187.topic&index=104>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Eh</span><hr size=1> Why not quit everyone's bitching my screwing over everybody's easy soloing in PoP.<br>
