<br>
So adjust the risk/reward ratio.  Make it more likely that charm will break.  Reduce the exp gained from charm soloing.  Hell, reduce the exp gained from soloing generally.  Make dying in PoP a little more costly, unless you get a rezz.  <br>
<br>
Anyone who has a problem with Verant re-balancing a particular class hasn't been paying attention.  Verant has been tweaking all sorts of aspects of the game since the very beginning, and class abilities are only one example.  We've all made choices (my particular pet peeve was when I decided to agnostic, only to find years later that new deity-specific armor was being introduced that kicks the crap out of the stuff agnostics can wear), and we've watched the consequences of those choices changed dramatically.  It's not as if these are immutable laws of nature that we are talking about. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aflacksaryrn>Aflack Saryrn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:yellow;'>Tavern Ale Swiller</span></span><br>  Posts: 86<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(4/3/03 9:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3187.topic&index=120>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing</span><hr size=1> Ok, I'm going to put in my 2 cents on this argument.  This talk of nerfing charm is nothing new.  Its been around for a few months now.   It still has yet to happen, came close a few times, just like it came close on the 1st.  <br>
<br>
I am much like Beth, I have played with charm since my Enchanter was level 16, maybe not as often as she has, but I have been using it.  Once they removed the penalty of XP gained on charms a while back I used it much more.  I remember soloing in the grey and getting very good xp there.  Also remember taking along friends to have a relaxed atmosphere to play with them.  <br>
<br>
Another few points, to say charming for insane amounts of xp is new with the addition to PoP isnt true at all.  I know Enchanters who at level 60 got a AA per 40 min at places like UP, charm fighting Elasians.  If you all remember back in those days that is a sick amount of xp for that time.  An &quot;good&quot; group will make a AA in a nice place every 2 hours.  Looks pretty comparative to what is seen now I'd say.  With the addition to PoP what do you see? Everyone is getting better XP, not just Enchanters who solo.  Let me say that again so those of you who are slow will understand.  EVERYONE IS GETTING BETTER EXPERIENCE POINTS PER KILL.  If you cut it down a lucky and supurb Enchanter will get a AA per 20 min (more like 30 min average time I'd say).  However at the same token, a good group in the right zone will make a AA point in 40 min or so.  Looks like the groups made a better xp bump than the soloing enchanter if you ask me.  So saying that Enchanters charm soloing for sick amounts of xp is something brand new in PoP is stupid.  Saying everyone is makeing better xp with PoP is really what its all about.  <br>
<br>
Honestly, I dont understand why more Enchanters didnt solo when the xp nerf was taken off at the beging baffles me, almost as much as why the ever knowing Nandarie would want her/his own class nerfed.  <br>
<br>
Another thing I want to point out, saying you make up the xp loss in one kill is just plain wrong as well, ( few of you tried to point this out).  Here is what I see.  When I die, I lose 6% of real xp, after that, when I turn on xp to 100% one kill in BoT will get me a mere 2.5% of solid xp.  I'm lost on this, how does 2.5 = 6?  Seems to me, I need around 3 kills to make up what I lost.  Also, when I die, I respawn with none of my gear and full mana.  Unfortunatly, my gear is around 60% of my mana.  After I buff myself I will be very OOM and need to med anyways.  If I get a rez, the downtime isnt that much longer.  Anyways, a death is at least 15 min of downtime for me (with rez maybe a 20 min downtime)<br>
<br>
Another stupid argument is the risk vs reward theory.  How much risk does a full group take versus a soloing player with charm.  More or less? If you answered more your stupid and should stop playing this game.  Whats the logic behind this?  Since a soloing Enchanter takes more risk, he very much deserves the xp that a full group should get (albeight he doesnt with the group xp bonuses).  As mentioned before, once I die, im looking at a 15 min downtime min anyways.  Dont give me this graveyard garbage because you have the same benifit as well in a group, but in a group a rez should be easier as your group will probably have a cleric.  A average charming Enchanter dies 1 out of 15 kills.  That sounds about right, how often does a group die once out of 15 kills?  If it did, your in a very sorry group.  Once again,  this points out the risk vs reward theory works in favor of the charming charactor.  <br>
<br>
To say a Enchanter is one of the holy trinity of a group, and them being taken out is of it is dumb.  Holy trinity for those of you who doesnt know is a Warrior, Enchanter, and Cleric.  How many warriors can be replaced by a Paladain, Shadow Knight, or even a Ranger with good gear?  How many Clerics are vital to a group that a Shaman or druid cannot fill?  How many Enchanters can be filled by a Shaman, Bard, Beast Lord, or Even a Ranger?  The holy trinity is something stupid that die hard EQ addicts invented, and is not the only way to make a good group.  Point: if a Enchanter does not want to join your group, then move on and find someone else who can fill in for him, its not that hard.  Beast Lords have a 65% slow wich is only 5% less effective as a Enchanters.  <br>
<br>
Also this topic that a Enchanter should not be a effective soloing class is stupid as well.  Who made you the damn almighty to say this?  Where you part of the dev team that created EQ?  If not then would you please stop sputing bulls.hit, your only making yourself look stupid.  Your basing this on a hunch and have no real proof.  Go find your stupid little book, and quote it.  Doesnt mean that the devs didnt design charm to be used the way it is now.  To make a quote like this, is because unfortunately you cannot think outside of the box that a lot of us Enchanters have.  Who said that all we are meant is to just sit there and be buff whores, and slow gimps for a group?  If that is all we where meant to be used for, then the original devs would have never introduced charms in the first place.  All throughout EQ, people have always thought of ways to work outside the box, Warriros soloing velks, Ranjors soloing PoV, ect ect.  Just because you are incapable of this, dont even start to burn the ones who are.  If you dont want to solo, then fine dont.  No one is making you.  <br>
<br>
All in all, I highly doubt the nerf is going to take place soon, its been talked and put off for a while.  If they do nerf it, then that will be the last straw for me.  VI will not see my 12 bucks a month anymore, and I'm very sure that a lot of Mages, Druids, and escpecially Enchanters will follow.   <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479240" target="top">Sage Aflack Dukky </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <br>
